{"question": "If I close my new savings account within 30 days of opening it, will I be charged a fee?", "answer": "Yes, you will be charged a $25 fee unless the closure is due to a Gemini Bank error in account opening, customer dissatisfaction with a product or service disclosed during the opening process, or insufficient funds.", "reasoning": "• Account Closure: A customer who closes their new savings account within 30 days of opening will be subject to a $25 fee unless the closure is due to:
Ο Gemini Bank error in account opening.
Ο Customer dissatisfaction with a product or service disclosed during the opening process.
Insufficient Funds: Customers will be notified of non-sufficient funds (NSF) fees according to the standard Gemini Bank NSF Fee Schedule."}
